@Node "About" "4D-Clock.guide/About"
@Toc "Main"

@{fg shine}About this program@{fg text}

4D-Clock is a simple analog clock which almost looks like the clock
shiped with AmigaOS. But it has a special feature: You can turn it
around via arrow keys in 3-dimensional space!

If you have a 3D accelerator card (e.g. CyberVision64/3D, CyberVisionPPC, Voodoo)
and Warp3D installed on your system, it also uses hardware accelerated 3D output.
See also @{" Requirements " Link "Requirements"}.

@endnode

@Node "Requirements" "4D-Clock.guide/Requirements"
@Toc "Main"

@{fg shine}Requirements@{fg text}

 - 68030 CPU and FPU or better
 - AmigaOS 3.5 or better
 - StormMesa 3.0 or better

Optional

 - 3D Accelerator
 - Warp3D


If you don't already have StormMesa, download it from:

  http://www.haage-partner.com/3dworld/index-e.htm

@endnode

@Node "ToolTypes" "4D-Clock.guide/ToolTypes"
@Toc "Main"

@{fg shine}ToolTypes@{fg text}

You can configure the clock via ToolTypes.
The following ToolTypes are available:


 @{b}- LEFT@{ub}

 Distance from the left screen border in pixel.
 Default is 100.


 @{b}- TOP@{ub}

 Distance from the top edge of the screen in pixel.
 Default is 100.


 @{b}- SECONDS@{ub}

 Toggle seconds pointer visibility.
 If this Tooltype exists, the secons pointer is visible.


 @{b}- WIDTH@{ub}

 Window width in pixel. Default is 200.


 @{b}- HEIGHT@{ub}

 Window height. Default is 200.


 @{b}- SEGMENTS@{ub}

 Defines in how many segments the disc will be seperated.
 The more segments, the smoother the disc looks like.
 You can even have a triangle clock!
 Default is 24.


 @{b}- XANGLE@{ub}

 X rotation angle in degrees. This is a floating point value.
 Default is -30.0.


 @{b}- YANGLE@{ub}

 Y rotation angle in degrees. This is a floating point value.
 Default is 0.0.

@endnode

@Node "Usage" "4D-Clock.guide/Usage"
@Toc "Main"

@{fg shine}Usage@{fg text}

Doubleclick the icon to start.
The window is scalable.
Use arrow keys to turn the clock around in 1 degree steps.

You can also configure the clock via @{" ToolTypes " Link "ToolTypes" }.


@endnode

